In order to compare both models, the allotetraploid and the autotetraploid, an analysis of the compounds content logFC respect to the diploid lines was performed. In the allotetraploid model, 4xAL2 showed increases for terpenes and non-isoprenoid compounds and decreases in amino acids, respect to the diploid 2xPIH. On the other hand, 4xAL4 behaved exactly in the opposite way (

). In the autotetraploid model the three lines showed smaller changes than the allotetraploids, except for line 4xAuL1 regarding amino acid content (

).

PCA analyses were performed for allotetraploids, autotetraploids and cultivated varieties separately and biplots projecting individuals and variables were obtained (

). The two allotetraploids 4xAL2 and 4xAL4 showed very contrasting behaviors and the diploid parental hybrid 2xPIH was intermediate between them (

). Amino acids were located around 4xAL4, while monoterpenes and most of the sesquiterpenes were nearby 4xAL2.

